With the help of a supervisor, the students analyze in the team work format a certain scientific problem using the suitable research articles published in English. The students compile an English summary characterizing the problem and present in at the seminar. Next, the students formulate a hypothesis considering the given scientific problem and plan a control experiment enabling verification of the proposed hypothesis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to give the students experience in the application of scientific method logics for the research work in the specialty field. Another goal is to develop the communication skills in the English language characteristic for the given specialty.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of this course, the student is expected to: 1. Have sufficient experience in the analysis of scientific problems as a part of team work based on the investigation of research articles published in English; 2. Be able to compile a referative summary of literature focussing on a certain scientific problem; 3. Within the defined limits, be able to successfully participate in a presentation held in English and summarizing a certain scientific problem; 4. Have efficiently participated in the team work aiming at the formulation of a hypothesis considering the proposed scientific problem and planning of the respective control experiment.
